[/list]

[heading]Runtime Validation[/heading]
The mod includes runtime validation logging. This helps players and testers confirm whether active settings were actually applied in-game.

The runtime log reports each setting as:
[list]
[*][b]applied[/b] - the active setting found its target and changed values.[/*]
[*][b]inactive[/b] - the setting is at vanilla/default value and was not applied.[/*]
[*][b]partial[/b] - some targets applied, but some fields or targets were missing.[/*]
[*][b]pending[/b] - the setting is waiting for the game to load the needed target.[/*]
[*][b]skipped[/b] - the setting was active but skipped by validation logic.[/*]
[*][b]unsupported[/b] - the setting is available in the UI but does not yet have a verified runtime target.[/*]
[/list]

For a clean validation pass, look for:
[code]VALIDATION GreenLight ... GreenLight=YES[/code]

A clean pass should also show:
[code]Partial=0 Pending=0 Skipped=0 Unsupported=0 MissingFields=0[/code]

If [b]GreenLight=NO[/b], check nearby [b]SETTING_STATUS[/b] lines to see which active setting needs attention.

[heading]Current Beta Notes[/heading]
[list]
[*]This [b]v0.1.7-beta[/b] build includes runtime safety fixes for carcass harvesting, free-craft/resource input handling, zero-value timer math, the Transfer Vault beta with cleaner player inventory names, persistent checked item rows, inventory dropdown browsing, read-only live prospect inventory item amounts, and restore slot safety checks.[/*]
[*]Skinning yield now increases carcass output counts instead of changing [b]D_ToolDamage.Skinning_Efficiency[/b], which could make carcasses deplete too quickly.[/*]
[*]Baseline 0 values now stay 0 during multiplier math, preventing disabled or sentinel timers from becoming one-second timers.[/*]
[*]Free craft no longer clears [b]ResourceInputs[/b], avoiding live resource drain behavior.[/*]
[*]Generic processor/material/free-craft array edits skip carcass processor rows.[/*]
[*]Stack and container slot mutations are clamped so runtime validation cannot shrink storage below vanilla baseline.[/*]
[/list]

[b]Important:[/b] Some values are table-backed rather than direct live-player writes. Health, stamina, carry capacity, movement speed, and regen mutate [b]D_CharacterStartingStats[/b] stat grants. Icarus may combine those with equipment, talents, buffs, current health, and spawn/session state, so the visible HUD may not always look like a simple old value times multiplier immediately. Fully restart Icarus and enter a session before judging runtime changes.

[heading]Important Safety Notes[/heading]
[list]
[*]The configurator automatically backs up saves before applying settings.[/*]
[*]Manual extra backups are still recommended before using inventory, stack, slot, backpack, free-craft, or recipe-array options.[/*]
[*]Lowering inventory or container slot values below current contents can risk item loss.[/*]
[*]Changing recipe inputs or outputs can affect crafting balance heavily.[/*]
[*]Some advanced options may appear in the configurator with warnings for testing purposes.[/*]
[*]The validator is designed to avoid fake green passes.[/*]
[/list]

[heading]Save Backups[/heading]
The [b]Save Backups[/b] tab manages Icarus player/world save backups. Backups are stored under [b]%LOCALAPPDATA%\ZSG Studios\IcarusConfigMod\save_backups[/b], not inside the extracted mod folder.

When present, backups include:
[list]
[*][b]Saved\PlayerData[/b][/*]
[*][b]Saved\SaveGames[/b][/*]
[*][b]Saved\ExtraData[/b][/*]
[*][b]Saved\steam_autocloud.vdf[/b][/*]
[/list]

Every apply creates a [b]before_apply[/b] backup first. Restoring a backup creates a [b]pre_restore[/b] backup before replacing matching save components. Close Icarus before creating or restoring backups so the app does not copy or replace live save files.

[heading]Transfer Vault[/heading]
The [b]Transfer Vault[/b] tab scans local Icarus player folders and prospect files. It has an inventory dropdown for clean one-inventory-at-a-time browsing, keeps checked item rows selected when switching inventories, and can move verified JSON-backed items, such as meta inventory/loadout items, into a shared offline stash under [b]%LOCALAPPDATA%\ZSG Studios\IcarusConfigMod\transfer_vault[/b].

[list]
[*]Creates a full save backup before vault export/import.[/*]
[*]Uses a [b]vault.lock[/b] file so two vault operations cannot run at the same time.[/*]
[*]Writes a transaction ledger to [b]transfer_vault\ledger.jsonl[/b].[/*]
[*]Refuses item moves while Icarus is open.[/*]
[*]Checks known target slot capacity before restore and refuses to write if no open slot is available.[/*]
[*]Detects active prospect members and decodes compressed live-world inventory item row names, amounts, cleaner owning inventory names, and player names read-only.[/*]
[*]Hides internal attachment, ammo-slot, and prospect-manager inventories from the dropdown.[/*]
[*]Separates same-name containers with unique suffixes so each dropdown option maps to one actual inventory.[/*]
[/list]

[b]Beta limit:[/b] live backpack, hotbar, belt, equipment, mount cargo, and world container items inside [b]ProspectBlob.BinaryBlob[/b] are listed read-only until the Unreal property writer is fully validated.

[heading]Installation Instructions[/heading]
[list=1]
[*]Download the release zip from the Files tab.[/*]
[*]Extract the zip anywhere outside the Icarus install folder.[/*]
[*]Run [b]IcarusConfigMod.exe[/b].[/*]
[*]Select [b]Vanilla Defaults[/b], [b]Premade_Configuration[/b], or import/create a custom profile.[/*]
[*]Click the install/apply button in the configurator.[/*]
[*]The configurator creates a player/world save backup before applying.[/*]
[*]If prompted, select your Icarus folder or [b]Icarus\Binaries\Win64[/b].[/*]
[*]Fully close and restart Icarus.[/*]
[*]Enter a session/prospect so the game loads the required runtime tables.[/*]
[*]Check the runtime validation log if you want to confirm a clean pass.[/*]
[/list]

[heading]Included Files[/heading]
[list]
[*][b]IcarusConfigMod.exe[/b] - portable Windows configurator and installer.[/*]
[*][b]UE4SS.dll[/b] - bundled UE4SS runtime DLL used by the installer.[/*]
[*][b]main.dll[/b] - compiled Configuration_Mod UE4SS C++ runtime DLL.[/*]
[*][b]Configuration_Mod/[/b] - runtime config, manifest, settings, and enabled marker.[/*]
[*][b]profiles/Premade_Configuration.json[/b] - included premade profile.[/*]
[*]Portable app runtime DLL/PYD files required by the standalone configurator.[/*]
[*][b]README.md[/b], [b]PLAYER_README.txt[/b], and [b]LICENSE[/b].[/*]
[/list]

[heading]Requirements[/heading]
[list]
[*]Icarus on Steam[/*]
[*]Windows[/*]
[*]No separate Python install required for players[/*]
[*]No batch or PowerShell scripts required for players[/*]
[*]Administrator permission may be required depending on where Steam/Icarus is installed[/*]
[/list]

[heading]Uninstall / Reset[/heading]
Open [b]IcarusConfigMod.exe[/b] and use [b]Reset Installed Mod[/b] from the console/actions area. You can also return to [b]Vanilla Defaults[/b] before removing the mod.

[heading]Custom Profiles[/heading]
[list]
[*]Use the configurator to save a profile.[/*]
[*]Imported profiles are copied into the local profiles folder.[/*]
[*]Profiles then appear directly in the profile dropdown.[/*]
[*]The dropdown shows clean names without .json.[/*]
[/list]

[heading]Known Notes[/heading]
[list]
[*]Vanilla Defaults is intentionally the first selected option on first launch.[/*]
[*]Premade_Configuration is the included balance preset.[/*]
[*]Runtime validation happens after Icarus loads enough game data.[/*]
[*]If you change settings while Icarus is running, fully restart the game before judging results.[/*]
[*]A clean validation log proves the target table/runtime value changed as expected, but derived stats may be recalculated by the game before they are visible on the current character.[/*]
[/list]

[heading]Third-Party Credits[/heading]
Built with UE4SS / RE-UE4SS and the UE4SS C++ Mod Template. UE4SS uses third-party dependencies including ImGui, glfw, glad, Zydis, PolyHook 2, asmjit, fmt, Tracy, and glaze. The configurator uses Python and Tkinter. All third-party tools and libraries remain credited to their respective authors and maintainers.

